title: Update jsonwebtoken typings for 6.2.0
body:
According to the jsonwebtoken [changelog](https://github.com/auth0/node-jsonwebtoken/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md), there were quite a few changes that need to be reflected in the type definition of the module.

For example, the callback for `jwt.sign()` now is a standard node callback with an `err, result` signature. In addition to that, some keys were renamed or removed after having been deprecated before.

title: Make nunjucks typings usable without AMD
body:
The existing typings were only usable when using modules. Using the
global `nunjucks` variable was not possible.

I used `js-yaml/js-yaml.d.ts` as an example of a typing that was usable
both as a module and as a global variable.

The indentation of the whole file was changed because the base
indentation used to be 2 (namespace inside module) and is now 1.

The existing test is working as is.
